olive oil
1 parsnip
1 clove garlic
1 head broccoli
1 bag chives
½ lemon
¼ tsp salt
30 g butter
1 packet salmon
3 potatoes

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
Cut the potato and parsnip into bite-sized chunks.
Place the veggies on a lined oven tray, drizzle with
olive oil and season with the salt and a pinch of
pepper. Toss to coat and roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, finely chop the
garlic. Cut the broccoli into small florets and
roughly chop the stalk. Finely chop the chives.
Halve the lemon.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a medium-high heat. Cook the broccoli, tossing,
until tender, 6-7 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help speed up
the cooking process.

When the veggies have 10 minutes roasting time
remaining, return the frying pan to a medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Pat the salmon dry
with paper towel, then season both sides. When
the oil is hot, cook the salmon, skin-side down
first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes on
each side (depending on thickness). Transfer to the
serving plates.

Return the frying pan to a low heat. Cook the
butter, garlic, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of
olive oil until the butter has melted and browned
slightly, 1-2 minutes. Add the chives and a
generous squeeze of lemon juice, then season
with pepper and stir to combine.

TIP: Butter can burn fast, so keep an eye on it!

TIP: Taste and add more lemon juice if you like.

Divide the golden roasted veggies and broccoli
between the serving plates of salmon. Spoon the
chive-lemon butter sauce over the salmon to serve.